#) This test tests the capabilities of the message box which layout
   its non-standard children.

#) A message box should appear, with a menubar, drawing area with scale,
   standard control buttons, plus an additional pushbutto, toggle button,
   arrow button and drawn button.
C)

#) Verify that the message box functions correctly.
C)

#) A Message Box should appear, created via XmCreateTemplateDialog.
#) The message box should have as its symbol, a pixmap of a mountain.
#) The message should read: "This is a test of the XmCreateTemplateDialog 
     function"
#) There should be a menu bar, with two pulldown menus labeled:
     Rocky Mountain and Hilly Mountain.
#) A Label contained within a RowColumn should appear in the middle
     region and should say "Eye, Yi Yi Yi...\n I am a Frito Bandito".
#) The buttons on the bottom of the message box should be in the
     following order:

      OK (pushbutton), Ticonderoga(pushbutton), 
      arrowbutton(pointing up), and Oh Susanna(drawnbutton), followed by
      the Cancel and Help buttons.

#) The ToggleButton 'Guide Dogs?' should be on the MenuBar.

C)

#) A Message Box should appear, create via XmCreateMessageBox with
   XmNdialogType set to XmDIALOG_TEMPLATE.
#) The message should read "This is a XmDIALOG_TEMPLATE XmNdialogType 
   MessageBox!\n  SMILE!".
#) The symbol should be the smiley face.
#) Buttons should be: Otay 'Panky, Watch the birdie!, Say Cheese..., Cancel,
   and Help.
#) A PanedWindow should appear above the buttons which has two panes;
   one allows the selection of camera type.  The other allows the
   selection of the style of poses.  A label should appear to the
   right of the PanedWindow, with string "I got a Nikon camera, I can
   take a photograph, Mama dont take my Kodachrome away..."

C)
#) A template dialog with no children has been created.
#) There should be no children visible!
C)
E)
